01:23:16,972 --> 01:23:20,464
and, you know,
we all end up in the same place.

1216
01:23:20,542 --> 01:23:21,907
Yeah.

1217
01:23:23,679 --> 01:23:24,941
There is no point.

1218
01:23:25,013 --> 01:23:27,743
There is no point.
That's what I'm saying.

1219
01:23:32,921 --> 01:23:34,445
You know,

1220
01:23:35,857 --> 01:23:38,985
I'm not normally the guy
you would talk to about stuff like this.

1221
01:23:43,131 --> 01:23:45,122
If you think about it,

1222
01:23:46,868 --> 01:23:51,305
your favourite memories, the most
important moments in your life,

1223
01:23:51,373 --> 01:23:52,931
were you alone?

1224
01:23:54,976 --> 01:23:56,500
No, I guess not.

1225
01:23:57,779 --> 01:24:01,510
Hey, come to think of it, last night,
the night before your wedding,

1226
01:24:01,583 --> 01:24:03,551
when all this shit
is swirling around in your head,

1227
01:24:03,618 --> 01:24:05,882
weren't you guys
sleeping in separate bedrooms?

1228
01:24:05,954 --> 01:24:07,785
Yeah, Julie went back to the apartment,

1229
01:24:07,856 --> 01:24:10,950
and I was just by myself
in the honeymoon suite.

1230
01:24:11,026 --> 01:24:14,223
-Kind of lonely?
-Yes, it was pretty lonely.

1231
01:24:16,064 --> 01:24:20,262
-Life's better with company.
-Yeah.

1232
01:24:21,370 --> 01:24:23,531
Everybody needs a co-pilot.

1233
01:24:25,607 --> 01:24:27,973
-That was a nice touch.
-Thanks.

1234
01:24:30,846 --> 01:24:35,010
-So, what's the mood like out there?
-It's not good.

1235
01:24:35,584 --> 01:24:38,178
-She's pretty pissed?
-She's upset.

1236
01:24:41,022 --> 01:24:42,683
What should I do?

1237
01:24:44,593 --> 01:24:45,992
Go get her.

1238
01:25:01,209 --> 01:25:03,973
I'm such a fuck-up. I love you so much.

1239
01:25:04,679 --> 01:25:06,670
Will you be my co-pilot?

1240
01:25:08,884 --> 01:25:10,852
Yes. Yes.

1241
01:25:16,591 --> 01:25:18,081
Welcome home.

1242
01:27:53,248 --> 01:27:55,978
Okay, this is your stop.

1243
01:28:03,425 --> 01:28:07,384
-When am I going to see you?
-You're just going to have to come visit.

1244
01:28:08,163 --> 01:28:09,755
So settled.

1245
01:28:11,466 --> 01:28:13,491
You're not going to change on me,
are you?

1246
01:28:13,568 --> 01:28:17,060
No. Same guy. Just one address.

1247
01:28:19,074 --> 01:28:20,371
This is your final boarding call

1248
01:28:20,442 --> 01:28:23,468
for American Airlines
flight number 3972 to Chicago.

1249
01:28:25,547 --> 01:28:28,243
All right. Call me when you get lonely.

1250
01:28:31,519 --> 01:28:32,918
I'm lonely.

1251
01:29:06,521 --> 01:29:08,250
Some guy sits down
in a conference room somewhere

1252
01:29:08,323 --> 01:29:11,884
and our server routes his session
to one of our termination engineers.

1253
01:29:11,960 --> 01:29:13,791
''Termination engineers''? Really?

1254
01:29:13,862 --> 01:29:16,353
I preferred ''terminators,''
but it bumped with Legal.

1255
01:29:16,431 --> 01:29:17,898
Can't imagine why.

1256
01:29:17,966 --> 01:29:19,957
They follow a workflow
that takes them through anything

1257
01:29:20,035 --> 01:29:21,593
from a standard dismissal
to a violent aggressor.

1258
01:29:21,670 --> 01:29:24,230
What are they doing now?
Are they practicing?

1259
01:29:24,305 --> 01:29:27,706
Well, beta testing, role-playing.
We go live at the end of the month.

1260
01:29:28,510 --> 01:29:30,705
Kyle, you're running through the events
too quickly.

1261
01:29:30,779 --> 01:29:32,940
You need to give them time
to acknowledge each statement, okay?

1262
01:29:33,014 --> 01:29:34,777
It's a legal thing.

1263
01:29:35,417 --> 01:29:37,749
-Ryan?
-Yeah. There's more?

1264
01:29:45,427 --> 01:29:47,019
This is ridiculous.

1265
01:29:47,095 --> 01:29:49,120
But, you know, Legal's really starting to
come hard at me

1266
01:29:49,197 --> 01:29:51,927
on this term ''terminate,'' so...

1267
01:30:30,405 --> 01:30:32,168
Ladies and gentlemen,
put your hands together

1268
01:30:32,240 --> 01:30:35,368
for today's challenge speaker,
Mr. Ryan Bingham.

1269
01:30:37,679 --> 01:30:39,146
Go get them.

1270
01:30:49,591 --> 01:30:52,685
Last year, I flew 350,000 miles.

1271
01:30:54,362 --> 01:30:56,023
The moon is 250.

1272
01:30:59,267 --> 01:31:03,761
I want you to imagine for a second
that you're carrying a backpack.

1273
01:31:03,838 --> 01:31:06,534
I want you to feel the straps
on your shoulders.

1274
01:31:07,475 --> 01:31:08,965
You feel them?

1275
01:31:10,578 --> 01:31:15,140
Now I want you to pack it with
all the stuff that you have in your life.

1276
01:31:16,651 --> 01:31:21,520
Start with the little things,
the things on shelves and in drawers.

1277
01:31:41,643 --> 01:31:43,110
Excuse me.

1278
01:31:46,748 --> 01:31:48,545
What the fuck are you doing?

1279
01:31:48,616 --> 01:31:50,709
Okay, everyone, just relax.

1280
01:32:15,777 --> 01:32:18,371
-Hey, you got to sign.
-Thought I did that already.

1281
01:32:19,747 --> 01:32:21,806
-Okay, thank you.
-All right.

1282
01:32:24,652 --> 01:32:28,019
Hey, you forgot to give me
your Hertz No.1 Gold Card!

1283
01:33:03,458 --> 01:33:05,688
So, I was in the neighbourhood.

1284
01:33:09,564 --> 01:33:11,725
Hey! Hey, wait! Wait, wait.

1285
01:33:20,742 --> 01:33:24,678
-Hey, honey, who's at the door?
-It's just somebody who's lost.

1286
01:34:23,638 --> 01:34:25,003
Alex?

1287
01:34:25,073 --> 01:34:28,042
What were you thinking,
showing up at my door like that?

1288
01:34:28,109 --> 01:34:30,270
What do you mean? I...
I wanted to see you.

1289
01:34:30,345 --> 01:34:33,314
I didn't know you had a family.
Why wouldn't you tell me that?

1290
01:34:33,381 --> 01:34:34,643
Look, I'm sorry I ruined your evening,

1291
01:34:34,716 --> 01:34:36,980
but, I mean, you could have seriously
screwed things up for me.

1292
01:34:37,051 --> 01:34:40,578
That's my family. That's my real life.

1293
01:34:43,691 --> 01:34:45,625
I thought I was a part of your real life.

1294
01:34:47,295 --> 01:34:49,422
I thought we signed up
for the same thing.

1295
01:34:51,499 --> 01:34:55,401
Try and help me understand
exactly what it is that you signed up for.

1296
01:34:56,771 --> 01:34:59,763
I thought our relationship
was perfectly clear.

1297
01:34:59,841 --> 01:35:03,743
I mean, you are an escape.

1298
01:35:06,381 --> 01:35:10,442
You're a break from our normal lives.
You're a parenthesis.

1299
01:35:14,255 --> 01:35:16,155
I'm a parenthesis?

1300
01:35:16,224 --> 01:35:17,452
I mean...

1301
01:35:18,326 --> 01:35:22,558
What do you want?
Tell me what you want.

1302
01:35:28,603 --> 01:35:30,594
You don't even know what you want.

1303
01:35:33,307 --> 01:35:35,298
I'm a grown-up, okay?

1304
01:35:35,710 --> 01:35:39,806
So, if you would like to see me again,
then give me a call.

1305
01:35:41,883 --> 01:35:42,975
Okay?

1306
01:35:59,434 --> 01:36:02,403
Ladies and gentlemen, we have
a special announcement to make.

1307
01:36:02,470 --> 01:36:06,907
Our pilot has just informed me that we
are passing over the city of Dubuque,

1308
01:36:06,974 --> 01:36:09,534
which might not mean much
to most of you,

1309
01:36:09,610 --> 01:36:12,170
but means a lot
to one of our flyers today.

1310
01:36:12,246 --> 01:36:17,149
-No.
-Because he just hit 10 million miles!

1311
01:36:20,855 --> 01:36:22,413
Congratulations.

1312
01:36:22,490 --> 01:36:26,017
-Such an amazing accomplishment.
-You must be very, very excited.

1313
01:36:26,727 --> 01:36:29,287
-Hi, Captain.
-Captain.

1314
01:36:29,397 --> 01:36:31,092
That seat taken?

1315
01:36:32,066 --> 01:36:33,397
No. No.

1316
01:36:40,608 --> 01:36:42,701
You're the youngest yet to hit 10 mil.

1317
01:36:44,045 --> 01:36:49,108
-Don't know where you found the time.
-Yeah. I don't know.

1318
01:36:50,818 --> 01:36:52,251
Yeah.

1319
01:36:55,389 --> 01:36:56,856
Here you go.

1320
01:36:59,160 --> 01:37:02,994
7th card we've made. Small club.

1321
01:37:06,467 --> 01:37:08,935
We really appreciate your loyalty.

1322
01:37:12,206 --> 01:37:15,107
You know how many times
I thought about this moment?

1323
01:37:17,478 --> 01:37:20,777
Played out the conversation
that you and I would have right here.

1324
01:37:20,882 --> 01:37:22,144
Really?

1325
01:37:25,219 --> 01:37:27,210
What did you want to say?

1326
01:37:32,226 --> 01:37:34,160
You know, I don't remember.

1327
01:37:36,564 --> 01:37:39,556
That's all right. It happens to all of us.

1328
01:37:44,038 --> 01:37:46,029
So, where are you from?

1329
01:37:52,180 --> 01:37:53,772
I'm from here.

1330
01:38:12,433 --> 01:38:14,128
Hello, Mr. Bingham.

1331
01:38:15,469 --> 01:38:18,597
-How did you know it was me?
-This is your dedicated line.

1332
01:38:18,673 --> 01:38:22,040
We reserve them for our most loyal
and appreciated flyers.

1333
01:38:22,109 --> 01:38:23,906
I'd like to transfer some of my miles.

1334
01:38:23,978 --> 01:38:27,141
Can I open up an account
to Jim and Julie Miller?

1335
01:38:27,782 --> 01:38:30,250
Certainly. How many miles
would you like to transfer?

1336
01:38:30,318 --> 01:38:32,980
How many miles does it take
to circle the globe?

1337
01:38:33,054 --> 01:38:37,184
We have our round-the-world tickets.
They're 500,000 miles each.

1338
01:38:37,258 --> 01:38:38,953
-That'd be fine.
-Got a second?

1339
01:38:39,026 --> 01:38:40,323
I'll call you back.

1340
01:38:40,394 --> 01:38:41,452
What the hell happened
to you yesterday?

1341
01:38:41,529 --> 01:38:43,190
I was trying to get hold of you all day.

1342
01:38:43,264 --> 01:38:46,700
I was... Some personal stuff.
What's going on?

1343
01:38:46,767 --> 01:38:49,065
Do you remember Karen Barnes,

1344
01:38:50,071 --> 01:38:53,666
part of a 30-person reduction
a few weeks back in Wichita?

1345
01:38:53,741 --> 01:38:55,504
Natalie fired her.

1346
01:38:56,077 --> 01:38:58,307
I fire dozens of people a day. I...

1347
01:38:58,379 --> 01:39:01,109
She killed herself, jumped off a bridge.

1348
01:39:03,184 --> 01:39:04,378
Fuck.

1349
01:39:04,852 --> 01:39:06,342
I need to know

1350
01:39:06,420 --> 01:39:10,413
if you remember any woman
that gave you any signals, depression...

1351
01:39:10,491 --> 01:39:12,049
They're all depressed.
We're firing them.

1352
01:39:12,126 --> 01:39:14,993
Hey, I need to ask you this stuff, okay?

1353
01:39:15,062 --> 01:39:19,158
No, I don't remember anything.
You never think that they're...

1354
01:39:21,769 --> 01:39:23,498
You don't remember any woman
that gave you any signals?

1355
01:39:23,571 --> 01:39:26,836
-Anything at all, Ryan?
-No, nothing stands out.

1356
01:39:30,611 --> 01:39:33,239
-Natalie all right?
-Natalie quit.

1357
01:39:37,518 --> 01:39:40,316
-She quit?
-Text message.

1358
01:39:42,056 --> 01:39:44,923
Yeah, fucking nice, right?
No one's got any manners anymore.

1359
01:39:46,027 --> 01:39:49,656
-She say where she was going?
-No. She was a little upset.

1360
01:39:52,066 --> 01:39:54,159
I should give her a call.

1361
01:39:57,271 --> 01:39:59,432
I need you back in the air.

1362
01:40:03,010 --> 01:40:06,537
Hey, did you hear what I said?
I thought you'd be thrilled about that.

1363
01:40:06,614 --> 01:40:09,174
It's fine.
What about the videoconferencing?

1364
01:40:09,250 --> 01:40:12,913
CTC is going to pause
the new-media front.

1365
01:40:12,987 --> 01:40:15,421
They're going to give it
some more thought.

1366
01:40:15,489 --> 01:40:17,423
We are going to get
our workhorses back in the air,

1367
01:40:17,491 --> 01:40:19,823
doing what they do best, okay?

1368
01:40:21,262 --> 01:40:25,426
-How long are you sending me out?
-We're going to let you sail and sail.

1369
01:40:25,499 --> 01:40:28,491
You send us a postcard
if you ever get there.

1370
01:40:42,583 --> 01:40:44,574
So, what happened?

1371
01:40:46,187 --> 01:40:50,146
-How exactly do you mean?
-You graduated top of your class.

1372
01:40:50,791 --> 01:40:53,487
You seemed to have your pick
of employment, including right here.

1373
01:40:53,561 --> 01:40:56,997
Instead you went to Omaha
to fire people for a living?

1374
01:40:59,100 --> 01:41:01,364
-It's challenging work.
-I'll say.

1375
01:41:02,536 --> 01:41:05,505
I can't imagine doing that day in,
day out.

1376
01:41:05,573 --> 01:41:07,336
Not in this climate.

1377
01:41:09,777 --> 01:41:11,438
I followed a boy.

1378
01:41:15,750 --> 01:41:18,412
Well, I guess everybody does that
at one point or another.

1379
01:41:24,792 --> 01:41:26,817
This guy says I'd be lucky to have you.

1380
01:41:27,294 --> 01:41:29,421
To whom it may concern,

1381
01:41:29,497 --> 01:41:32,728
I can't even count the number of people
I've fired in my lifetime.

1382
01:41:32,800 --> 01:41:36,634
So many that I've actually forgotten
what it's like to hire somebody.

1383
01:41:36,704 --> 01:41:40,663
We've never met, but I know
you'd be lucky to have Natalie Keener.

1384
01:41:41,542 --> 01:41:44,477
My advice?
Take her and don't look back.

1385
01:41:44,545 --> 01:41:47,412
She'll be the best decision
you've made in a long time.

1386
01:41:51,952 --> 01:41:53,920
I sure hope he's right.

1387
01:42:05,332 --> 01:42:07,425
Well, I don't have a lot of hope,

1388
01:42:07,501 --> 01:42:10,231
and I really don't know
when it's going to get better.

1389
01:42:10,304 --> 01:42:13,102
There's a lot of people unemployed,

1390
01:42:13,174 --> 01:42:17,270
and I really don't know when there's
going to be light at the end of the tunnel.

1391
01:42:17,812 --> 01:42:20,076
I can't find much to talk about.

1392
01:42:20,147 --> 01:42:22,513
Talk about being proud.
I'm proud of my kids.

1393
01:42:22,583 --> 01:42:28,044
I think the anger comes from the fact
that I just wasn't needed anymore.

1394
01:42:28,122 --> 01:42:30,056
I would say, you know,

1395
01:42:30,758 --> 01:42:34,854
without my friends and my family,
I wouldn't have made it.

1396
01:42:34,929 --> 01:42:37,727
It would have been a lot tougher if
I would have had to make it on my own.

1397
01:42:37,798 --> 01:42:41,791
When I wake up in the morning
and I look over and I see my wife,

1398
01:42:43,304 --> 01:42:44,862
that gives me the sense of purpose.

1399
01:42:44,939 --> 01:42:48,067
It's not all about the money.
Money can keep you warm.

1400
01:42:48,142 --> 01:42:51,543
It pays your heating bills, you know.
It can buy you a blanket.

1401
01:42:53,080 --> 01:42:57,107
But it's not as... Doesn't keep you as
warm as when my husband holds me.

1402
01:42:57,885 --> 01:43:01,548
Let me get up. Let me get out.
Let me find something.

1403
01:43:03,190 --> 01:43:06,318
So, my kids are my purpose, my family.

1404
01:43:36,457 --> 01:43:38,482
Tonight most people
will be welcomed home

1405
01:43:38,559 --> 01:43:41,084
by jumping dogs and squealing kids.

1406
01:43:42,229 --> 01:43:46,131
Their spouses will ask about their day,
and tonight they'll sleep.

1407
01:43:47,134 --> 01:43:50,934
The stars will wheel forth
from their daytime hiding places.

1408
01:43:52,606 --> 01:43:56,269
And one of those lights,
slightly brighter than the rest,

1409
01:43:56,343 --> 01:43:58,777
will be my wingtip passing over.

1410
01:46:09,677 --> 01:46:11,645
Hi, Jason. My name is Kevin,

1411
01:46:11,712 --> 01:46:14,112
and I recently lost my job.

1412
01:46:15,182 --> 01:46:20,051
I wrote this song as sort of
a statement about uncertainty

1413
01:46:20,120 --> 01:46:23,647
and having a certain amount of anxiety
about the future.

1414
01:46:25,225 --> 01:46:27,921
So, maybe you can use it in your movie.

